{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"J. Pedro Ribeiro","author":"J. Pedro Ribeiro"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"5ab2b2ea-31a8-5eae-b84c-a195730ecc92","excerpt":" I’ve build a small tool a while ago to help me align elements on a page and keep the baseline consistent. It adds a customisable horizontal grid layer on top…","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bc0a46ddd0701d679630f03a27080b08/135ae/baseliner-300x187.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 300px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 62.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Baseliner in action\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/bc0a46ddd0701d679630f03a27080b08/135ae/baseliner-300x187.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bc0a46ddd0701d679630f03a27080b08/cf440/baseliner-300x187.png 148w,\n/static/bc0a46ddd0701d679630f03a27080b08/d2d38/baseliner-300x187.png 295w,\n/static/bc0a46ddd0701d679630f03a27080b08/135ae/baseliner-300x187.png 300w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n     I’ve build a small tool a while ago to help me align elements on a page and keep the baseline consistent. It adds a customisable horizontal grid layer on top of any site whilst keeping the background content usable.</p>\n<p>It started as a simple CSS snippet: <code class=\"language-text\">background</code> repeated every 8px. Later it became a JavaScript bookmarklet since I needed to run it frequently. Then, added some <code class=\"language-text\">input</code> fields to let me change the grid value dynamically.</p>\n<p>Chrome it’s one of my tools of choice when doing web development work. Using extensions too. Almost every front-end engineer has a range of extensions that are essential. Managing cookies, cache, enable/disable features, storage, etc. So moving this tool to an extension environment sounded like the next logical step.</p>\n<p>It is a simple tool and it does the job it’s meant to. Nothing more, nothing less.</p>\n<p>You can find it at the Chrome Web Store, link is here: <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/baseliner/agoopbiflnjadjfbhimhlmcbgmdgldld\">https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/baseliner/agoopbiflnjadjfbhimhlmcbgmdgldld</a></p>\n<p>All feedback is welcome. You can reach me at <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jpedroribeiro\">@jpedroribeiro</a>.</p>\n<p>PS: All the source code is freely available at <a href=\"https://github.com/jpedroribeiro/Baseliner\">github.com/jpedroribeiro</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Baseliner: My First Chrome Extension","date":"August 30, 2015"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2015/08/baseliner-my-first-chrome-extension/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2015/07/being-technical-book-reviewer/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Being a Technical Book Reviewer"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2015/10/workflow-from-design-to-the-browser/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Workflow: From Design to the Browser"}}}}